Michelin and Fesvial together for helmet use
The manufacturer of tires Michelin, with the collaboration of the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to promote the use of the helmet, mainly among younger motorists, reported today both entities.
This initiative seeks to raise awareness about the importance of using the helmet, since it is the only element of protection capable of avoiding head injuries or even death in the event of an accident while riding a motorcycle.
Michelin said that this campaign is part of its commitment to road safety, which “goes beyond designing and manufacturing safer products every day” and affirmed that it also contributes to this goal through other educational and informative actions.
This new campaign to promote the use of the helmet on the motorcycle, under the slogan 'To be or not to be', will have a first phase in which posters will be distributed in more than 500 motorcycle workshops, with the aim of achieving maximum dissemination.
Finally, Michelin stressed that road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, since being a manufacturer of tires for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main purposes is to develop increasingly safer products.
