How much should you charge for your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can know the salary they deserve according to their profile, thanks to a new application of Trovit, the search engine with the highest number of classified ads of real estate, employment and motor in Spain.
The How much should you charge? tool calculates the salaries of users from the more than 140,000 job offers available to Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where they must enter their profession, years of experience, age and city where they want to work.
In the week that the application has been in operation, the search engine has detected that in general the Spanish worker "feels poorly paid," explained in a statement the head of product Trovit, Albert Ribera.
According to the data available to Trovit from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, Spaniards are the lowest paid.
A British computer programmer charges 45,226 euros gross per year and a French one, 31,059, compared to the 24,000 that a Spanish one receives.
In the same way, a driver charges 34,247 euros net per year in England, 25,751 in France and 16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest-paid job in Spain is that of a waiter, with 11,592 euros net per year; followed by that of a dependent, with 14,725 euros; and that of an operator, with 15,667 euros.
The most searched jobs in the network in the last three months are the driver, part-time jobs and social worker.
